SIMPLE: lowbell
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lowbell
<hw>Low"bell`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Low</ets> a
flame + <ets>bell</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A bell used in fowling
at night, to frighten birds, and, with a sudden light, to make them fly
into a net.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fowler's <qex>lowbell</qex> robs the lark of sleep.</q>
<rj><qau>King.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bell to be hung on the neck of a sheep.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>lowbell</qex> hung about a sheep's . . . neck.</q>
<rj><qau>Howell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lowbell</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lowbell
<hw>Low"bell`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To frighten, as with a
lowbell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lowborn</ent>⟦br⟧
